The guests were speaking during the African Tourism Investment Summit at the Cape Town International Convention Centre in South Africa yesterday. Authorities said the removal of travel restrictions is the basis for economic growth and job creation. Western Cape Economic Opportunities Minister, David Maynier, said the strong theme that has emerged is the need for air connectivity. “So we are investing in air connectivity making sure that our countries and our cities are open to tourists”, said Maynier. He said Africa needs to make investments in ensuring that air transport is open and form strong links as a region. African tourism economy has been heavily hit by the coronavirus pandemic.  --SABC-- 